  "title": "Nvidia Q1 2026 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2026-05-28T20:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2026_Q1",
  "location": "Santa Clara, CA",
  "url": "https://investor.nvidia.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "jensen-huang",
      "speaker_name": "Jensen Huang",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q1 2026 data center revenue was $44.2 billion, slightly ahead of guidance, as Rubin systems began early customer shipments in April. The Rubin ramp is tracking to plan and we expect to exit Q2 at volume. Physical AI — robotics, autonomous vehicles, and industrial automation — is emerging as a new growth vector. Our Isaac and DRIVE platforms have over 400 companies building on them. We expect physical AI revenue to reach $5 billion in fiscal 2027."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "colette-kress",
      "speaker_name": "Colette Kress",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Total Q1 2026 revenue was $49.1 billion, up 11% year-over-year, reflecting the expected Rubin transition dip. Gross margin recovered to 74.3%. Operating margin was 67.9%. For Q2, we expect revenue of $58 billion, plus or minus 2%, as Rubin volume ramps and demand from hyperscalers returns to prior trajectory."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Ben Reitzes at Melius Research."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-ben-reitzes",
      "speaker_name": "Ben Reitzes",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Jensen, physical AI at $5 billion in fiscal 2027 — is that already in contracted backlog or is it primarily design-win pipeline that still needs to convert to revenue?"
    }
  ],
